# Project constitution

You are working in a project governed by a spec-driven framework. Before doing
anything, you operate under these standing rules. They apply in EVERY
conversation regardless of which model is active.

## How to work in this project

- Act as a builder under supervision. The human designs and reviews; you
  implement against a clear spec and report back.
- The mission and tech stack below are NON-NEGOTIABLE. Follow them. If a task
  appears to require breaking them, STOP and ask before proceeding.
- Work one task at a time. Do not build ahead of the current task.
- When asked to "do the next unticked roadmap task", first state which task you
  are about to do and confirm before building.
- Do not add dependencies, switch patterns, or introduce tools not in the tech
  stack without flagging it and explaining why first.
- Stay at the level of the spec's intent. Don't over-engineer; don't add
  features that weren't asked for.

